Magic items are divided into categories: armor, weapons, potions, rings, rods, scrolls, staffs, wands, and wondrous items. In addition, some magic items are cursed or intelligent. Fin
ally, a few magic items are of such rarity and power that they are considered to belong to a category of their own: artifacts. Artifacts are classified in turn as minor (extremely rare but not one-of-a-kind items) or major (each one unique and extremely p
otent).
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\fs20\cf0 Armor and Shields:}{\fs20\cf0 
 Magic armor (including shields) offers improved, magical protection to the wearer. Some of these items confer abilities beyond a benefit to Armor Class. 
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Weapons:}{\fs20\cf0  Magic weapons are created with a variety of combat powers and almost always improve the attack and damage rolls of the wielder as well.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Potions:}{\fs20\cf0  A potion is an elixir concocted with a spell-like effect that affects only the drinker.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Rings:}{\fs20\cf0  A ring is a circular metal band worn on the finger (no more than two rings per wearer) that has a spell-like power (often a constant effect that affects the wearer).
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Rods: }{\fs20\cf0 A rod is a scepter-like item with a special power unlike that of any known spell.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Scrolls:}{\fs20\cf0  A scroll is a spell magically inscribed onto paper or parchment so that it can be used later.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Staffs:}{\fs20\cf0  A staff has a number of different (but often related) spell effects. A newly created staff has 50 charges, and each use of the staff depletes one or more of those charges.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Wands:}{\fs20\cf0  A wand is a short stick imbued with the power to cast a specific spell. A newly created wand has 50 charges, and each use of the wand depletes one of those charges.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Wondrous Items:}{\fs20\cf0  These objects include magic jewelry, tools, books, clothing, and much more.
\par }{\fs37\cf0 
